”

A menacing epidemic has brought the biggest crisis ever to players of all sizes on the shared charger circuit.

Unlike other Internet projects, the business model for sharing chargers relies heavily on offline merchants, who can not place valid orders for sharing chargers as long as they are not open.

Since the beginning of the epidemic, KTV, Internet cafes, Bathing Center and other entertainment venues have been suspended, catering, hotels are left empty. It's a near-death blow for an industry that relies heavily on human traffic, like chargers.

Recently, Xiaodian Technology CEO Tang Yongbo issued an open letter. The letter said the outbreak had dealt a fatal blow to the company's business, which had suffered a sharp drop in revenue while it had 5,000 employees whose salaries and other expenses such as supply chain and local office rents to deal with.

If the outbreak continues into March, it will affect not only the first quarter's results, but the industry's confidence in the industry as a whole.

But now, the inflection point of the epidemic has not yet clearly appeared, in order to save themselves, many enterprises have also begun the urgent measures to reduce expenditure.

One company has opted to withhold half of its January salary until February 20, while February and March salaries are normally paid with a base salary, while performance and commission payments are delayed until June, according to interface journalists.

Cheng Xiao is a business BD of the above company. According to its introduction, at present, the company in addition to a small number of administrative, public relations, technical colleagues have been through the remote online way to start standby, other offline BD are all in vacation state. "Hr just told us to look at the local epidemic situation, to come at the request of the local government, and to stay put without notice. But looking at this situation, I don't think the day for me to go to work is far off. "

In the industry, Cheng Xiao's company has been in the forefront of the track. Head enterprise is still so difficult, other small and medium-sized enterprises can be expected to share charging treasure days.

In fact, chargers have been the only track in the sharing economy that has been able to turn a large profit. In March 2019, the street electricity COO he shun has said in an interview with the media, the head Gamer is basically a profit. But after the street electricity, "three electricity a beast" the remaining enterprise also announces the profit one after another.

But an epidemic has dealt a fatal blow to the industry.

Once the upstream merchants'flow of people can not be protected, charging treasure as a downstream, will be seriously affected. In addition, charging treasure also to the merchant to pay a low rent or admission fees.

Wu Shichun, a founding partner of the angel of Plum Blossoms, once told the interface that sharing chargers is a low margin business model in itself, and as merchants'appetites get bigger, their profit margins will be squeezed smaller and smaller. And that affects the company's cash-flow reserves.

Last year, Cheng Xiao's company spent $20 million for the exclusive rights of a nightclub chain for three years. And similar things abound in the industry, in his view, this is the company's current cash flow is one of the reasons.

It is understood that in order to obtain more admission fees, many chain restaurants will even use the way of bidding to choose a cooperative partner to share charging. This is clearly the beginning of inefficient competition in the industry. The sudden outbreak of the crisis, may also prompt companies to think about the drawbacks of such models and efforts to find new profit models.

It is not clear how long the outbreak will last, but it is certain that the real economy will have to go through a long period of rebuilding confidence, whether it will be able to survive, every offline service enterprises must face the big test of life and death.
